examples.en: He was tall, dark and handsome.
My teacher is handsome, strictly!
Handsome is as handsome does.
He looked so handsome in his suit.
I predict that someone tall, dark, and handsome is going to come into your life.
He wrote an uncommonly handsome hand.
Sam was tall, dark and handsome.
The book brings in handsome royalties.
It was a handsome house situated on a large lot.
He inherited a handsome fortune.
The book is a handsome tribute to a great poet.
My boss could hardly be described as handsome.
He was handsome and nicely dressed.
He looked very handsome in his uniform.
They won a handsome victory in the elections.
He managed to make a handsome profit out of the deal.
They treated him to a handsome drubbing.
He did some handsome maneuvers on the skating rink.
She fell into a swoon at the sight of the handsome movie star.
A frown marred his handsome features.
He was handsomely rewarded by the king.
The book includes many handsome illustrations.
His handsome profile was turned away from the company.
A lanky kid transformed almost overnight into a handsome young man.
Whereas he had received a very handsome fortune with his wife, he had now spent every penny of it.
The handsome actor's vanity was well-known.
He made a handsome profit on the sale of the house.
She secured the zoo's future with a handsome bequest.
I was shocked to see the worn look of his handsome young face.
He's very handsome, with strong regular features (=an evenly shaped face).
